                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d357">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.113 Senate Investigation/60: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-09-22T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 22, 1934—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 23—10:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>166. Further supplementing my 163, September 20, 6 p.m., the Minister for Foreign
                    Affairs today told me that he considered the matter as now ended; that within a
                    fortnight local public opinion would have cooled down and the matter be
                    forgotten.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Weddell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
